Author: Phil_Bardsley
Title: 🚀[ANN] [WIKI] [ICO] WIKIBITS The First Blockchain-based Solution-driven Wiki 🚀
Body: Thank you, may I ask. What is the differences you would say between this and Lunyr? I think this is very important

Author: knowledge101
Title: 🚀[ANN] [WIKI] [ICO] WIKIBITS The First Blockchain-based Solution-driven Wiki 🚀
Body: Hi Phil, from a reward standpoint, we are very similar.  But to what we are trying to accomplish is vastly different:  I think we can all agree that the amount of information that is available have expanded tremendously, however, relevant information to the user's questions is currently scattered and often times lacking in evaluation of its effectiveness.  We are building a community knowledge base as well as leveraging on existing knowledge bases out there.  Process the data using Natural Language Processing and tabulate the results so that the users that use our portal can get an immediate, objective and community vested answer to his/her problem at hand.  We are filling in the inference gap that users currently experience when he or she searches for solutions across multiple portals such as yahoo answers, quora, answers.com etc  Lunyr and Wikibits both have a working Alpha, however, we diverge in our vision to utilize that knowledge base.  I hope that answers your question?

Author: lizdicrasco
Title: 🚀[ANN] [WIKI] [ICO] WIKIBITS The First Blockchain-based Solution-driven Wiki 🚀
Body: Quote from: knowledge101 on January 25, 2018, 11:25:51 AM Quote from: Phil_Bardsley on January 25, 2018, 11:14:56 AM Quote from: knowledge101 on January 25, 2018, 10:59:40 AM Quote from: Phil_Bardsley on January 25, 2018, 10:33:55 AM If I wish to post an article at this moment in time, I must have contributed to the current pre-sale of 1 ETH?  Hi Phil, you may post an article at this time. We will send you the 500 WIKI tokens if your article is accepted. However, the other bonus tokens you may earn on a daily basis will not be tabulated until you have made the minimum contribution either during presale or ICO  Thank you, may I ask. What is the differences you would say between this and Lunyr? I think this is very important  Hi Phil, from a reward standpoint, we are very similar.  But to what we are trying to accomplish is vastly different:  I think we can all agree that the amount of information that is available have expanded tremendously, however, relevant information to the user's questions is currently scattered and often times lacking in evaluation of its effectiveness.  We are building a community knowledge base as well as leveraging on existing knowledge bases out there.  Process the data using Natural Language Processing and tabulate the results so that the users that use our portal can get an immediate, objective and community vested answer to his/her problem at hand.  We are filling in the inference gap that users currently experience when he or she searches for solutions across multiple portals such as yahoo answers, quora, answers.com etc  Lunyr and Wikibits both have a working Alpha, however, we diverge in our vision to utilize that knowledge base.  I hope that answers your question?  I have the same Q. Thank you for the clear answer
